# This function is required to compute the mean value of each row in the given pandas DataFrame.
# The mean value is then added as a new column named 'mean' to the DataFrame.
def compute_mean_along_rows(df):
    # Compute the mean value along each row (axis=1) of the DataFrame.
    # Assign these mean values to a new column in the DataFrame named 'mean'.
    df['mean'] = df.mean(axis=1)
    return df
